WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.412 --> 00:00:15.182
Isaac. The voting for
class president has concluded.

2
00:00:15.315 --> 00:00:17.685
And? Don't keep me waiting. man.

3
00:00:17.819 --> 00:00:19.453
What were the results?

4
00:00:19.587 --> 00:00:22.189
-Well. you: one.
-Oh. I won?!

5
00:00:22.322 --> 00:00:24.358
I shall write
to Father immediately.

6
00:00:24.491 --> 00:00:27.160
Huzzah! What a day
to be Isaac Higgintoot.

7
00:00:27.294 --> 00:00:28.362
Oh...

8
00:00:28.495 --> 00:00:30.565
Oh. no.
Yes. that is my mistake.

9
00:00:30.698 --> 00:00:33.835
I was saying. "You. colon. one."

10
00:00:33.968 --> 00:00:36.069
The number one.
O-N-E.

11
00:00:36.203 --> 00:00:38.540
-What?
-You received one vote.

12
00:00:38.673 --> 00:00:40.374
Ebenezer Hubbard
received the rest.

13
00:00:40.508 --> 00:00:41.910
So. you: one.

14
00:00:42.042 --> 00:00:44.311
Ebenezer Hubbard: all the rest.

15
00:00:44.444 --> 00:00:46.079
Why would you say it like that?

16
00:00:46.213 --> 00:00:47.882
And surely you miscounted.

17
00:00:48.016 --> 00:00:49.517
I must have received two votes.

18
00:00:49.651 --> 00:00:52.219
One cast by myself
and the other by you.

19
00:00:52.352 --> 00:00:53.555
my roommate.

20
00:00:54.556 --> 00:00:56.558
It's just that Ebenezer Hubbard
was offering more pudding

21
00:00:56.691 --> 00:00:58.158
-in the dining hall.
-Oh!

22
00:00:58.292 --> 00:01:00.862
You and your single-issue
pudding voting.

23
00:01:00.995 --> 00:01:02.564
You know that's a treat
for children?

24
00:01:02.697 --> 00:01:04.231
You have a problem. sir.

25
00:01:04.364 --> 00:01:07.067
I'm sorry.
I'm just upset.

26
00:01:08.836 --> 00:01:10.905
You know what makes me
feel better when I'm upset?

27
00:01:11.873 --> 00:01:13.073
Don't say pudding.

28
00:01:18.211 --> 00:01:19.446
<i>Oh! Uh. Is it</i>

29
00:01:19.581 --> 00:01:21.015
-smaller than a breadbox?
-Yeah.

30
00:01:21.148 --> 00:01:22.917
Is it a Dane's head again?

31
00:01:23.051 --> 00:01:25.252
Ha! You are
most excellent guesser.

32
00:01:26.486 --> 00:01:28.590
Guys. this was so much fun.

33
00:01:28.723 --> 00:01:31.258
I can't believe we've never done
a double date before.

34
00:01:31.391 --> 00:01:33.595
Girl. we've done this
many times before.

35
00:01:33.728 --> 00:01:35.262
Oh. Right on.

36
00:01:35.395 --> 00:01:38.032
What is this? You guys have been
going on double dates?

37
00:01:38.165 --> 00:01:39.366
Apparently.

38
00:01:39.499 --> 00:01:41.703
Well. till next time.

39
00:01:45.573 --> 00:01:48.910
Why haven't you guys invited me
and Bela to these group dates?

40
00:01:49.043 --> 00:01:50.143
We're another couple
in the house.

41
00:01:50.277 --> 00:01:53.280
Well... kind of.

42
00:01:53.413 --> 00:01:55.550
You can only see her when you
visit her in her dreams.

43
00:01:55.683 --> 00:01:57.819
Yeah. no disrespect. but

44
00:01:57.952 --> 00:01:59.319
you guys are sort of
a night couple.

45
00:01:59.453 --> 00:02:01.556
-And we love that for you.
-Look.

46
00:02:01.689 --> 00:02:04.626
I know my thing with Bela
is unconventional.

47
00:02:04.759 --> 00:02:06.326
I mean. our last date

48
00:02:06.460 --> 00:02:08.428
took place in a hot air balloon
floating over Mars.

49
00:02:08.563 --> 00:02:11.633
But our relationship is just
as real as anyone else's.

50
00:02:13.534 --> 00:02:15.302
Okay. Sass.

51
00:02:15.435 --> 00:02:17.304
Would. uh. you and Bela
like to go on a double date

52
00:02:17.437 --> 00:02:20.808
with me and Pete later?
Say. after we smell lunch?

53
00:02:20.942 --> 00:02:23.477
We'd love to. Oh. and let us
know if we can bring anything.

54
00:02:23.611 --> 00:02:26.179
because my girlfriend
can carry stuff.

55
00:02:26.313 --> 00:02:27.314
Ooh.

56
00:02:27.447 --> 00:02:29.449
Sounds great. We're excited.

57
00:02:29.584 --> 00:02:31.686
-How is this gonna work?
-I have no idea.

58
00:02:33.788 --> 00:02:36.356
Yes. I'm sorry. Mrs. Stevens.
but we are aware.

59
00:02:36.490 --> 00:02:38.526
and we're working on
the hot water issue right now.

60
00:02:38.660 --> 00:02:41.829
You know. a lot of high-end spas
offer a cold plunge

61
00:02:41.963 --> 00:02:44.464
that guests actually
pay extra for...

62
00:02:44.599 --> 00:02:46.501
And she hung up on me.

63
00:02:46.634 --> 00:02:47.969
As a former penny stock slinger.

64
00:02:48.102 --> 00:02:50.170
I appreciate the attempt
to polish that turd.

65
00:02:50.303 --> 00:02:51.839
Well done.

66
00:02:51.973 --> 00:02:53.608
You know. it's great
that we're getting more guests

67
00:02:53.741 --> 00:02:54.709
since we got on that
boutique hotels list.

68
00:02:54.842 --> 00:02:56.376
but I'm a little worried

69
00:02:56.511 --> 00:02:57.879
about the strain it's putting
on the old water heater.

70
00:02:58.012 --> 00:03:01.281
Thor not understand
why anyone need hot bath.

71
00:03:01.415 --> 00:03:02.684
Or bath.

72
00:03:02.817 --> 00:03:05.053
Uh. one of my greatest
pleasures in life

73
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:08.523
was indulging in a hot bath.
The steam. the solitude.

74
00:03:08.656 --> 00:03:11.059
the pained grunts
of my servants as they

75
00:03:11.191 --> 00:03:12.727
lugged the boiling water
up three flights of stairs.

76
00:03:12.860 --> 00:03:14.829
Didn't you have
some big epiphany last week.

77
00:03:14.962 --> 00:03:17.197
something about a newfound
respect for the working man?

78
00:03:17.330 --> 00:03:18.900
Did I?
That does sound familiar.

79
00:03:19.033 --> 00:03:22.202
Hello. all.
Happy election day.

80
00:03:22.335 --> 00:03:24.005
Oh. that's right.
Today's the day

81
00:03:24.138 --> 00:03:26.339
those cretins downstairs
choose their nominee

82
00:03:26.473 --> 00:03:28.308
- for ghost representative.
- Yes.

83
00:03:28.442 --> 00:03:30.343
If I win this.
and then later. I best Flower

84
00:03:30.477 --> 00:03:33.715
in the general election.
the office is mine.

85
00:03:33.848 --> 00:03:36.216
Samantha. what's going on?
You're not wearing your button.

86
00:03:36.349 --> 00:03:39.219
Well. I was wearing it.
but then guests kept asking

87
00:03:39.352 --> 00:03:41.055
what "Isaac For
Ghost Representative" meant.

88
00:03:41.189 --> 00:03:42.590
and I didn't really
have a good answer.

89
00:03:42.724 --> 00:03:44.391
What does ghost representative
even do again?

90
00:03:44.525 --> 00:03:47.695
Is ghost who speak with Sam
on behalf of other ghosts.

91
00:03:47.829 --> 00:03:49.997
Dates back
to early days when Sam

92
00:03:50.131 --> 00:03:52.200
gain ability to see ghosts.

93
00:03:52.332 --> 00:03:53.901
but now more
of a figurehead position.

94
00:03:54.035 --> 00:03:56.336
Exactly. I've always
wanted to be a figurehead.

95
00:03:56.470 --> 00:03:58.539
Oh. I'm so nervous.

96
00:03:58.673 --> 00:04:01.743
I stand on the precipice of
my first-ever election victory.

97
00:04:01.876 --> 00:04:04.579
I don't understand how
this thing is even close.

98
00:04:04.712 --> 00:04:06.581
Isn't your opponent
literally named Creepy Dirk?

99
00:04:06.714 --> 00:04:09.449
Mm. down there.
creepiness isn't a liability.

100
00:04:09.584 --> 00:04:11.384
It's just something
that makes you relatable.

101
00:04:11.519 --> 00:04:14.922
Hey. babe. Mark and I were just
working on the water heater.

102
00:04:15.056 --> 00:04:16.724
Well. Mark was working.

103
00:04:16.858 --> 00:04:19.927
Jay just held the flashlight
and screamed. "Aah! Cobweb!"

104
00:04:20.061 --> 00:04:22.764
It's bad news.
You're gonna need a new unit.

105
00:04:22.897 --> 00:04:24.699
Yeah. we're gonna
need a new unit. babe.

106
00:04:24.832 --> 00:04:26.567
A new water heater?

107
00:04:26.701 --> 00:04:28.603
Samantha. that's not going to
go over well in the basement.

108
00:04:28.736 --> 00:04:30.204
They love that water heater.

109
00:04:30.337 --> 00:04:32.940
Are you sure we can't just
repair the current unit?

110
00:04:33.074 --> 00:04:34.942
Unfortunately. no.
But the good news is

111
00:04:35.076 --> 00:04:36.309
I can get you a new one
pretty quick.

112
00:04:36.443 --> 00:04:39.113
Yeah.
Yep. we can get it expedited.

113
00:04:39.247 --> 00:04:41.916
-Please stop doing that.
-Okay.

114
00:04:42.850 --> 00:04:44.819
Jay. this isn't good.

115
00:04:44.952 --> 00:04:46.621
The basement ghosts
are really attached

116
00:04:46.754 --> 00:04:48.990
-to that old water heater.
-Why?

117
00:04:49.123 --> 00:04:50.457
It's basically their god.

118
00:04:50.591 --> 00:04:52.126
Why?

119
00:04:52.260 --> 00:04:53.895
Why did the ancients
revere Zeus?

120
00:04:54.028 --> 00:04:55.428
Why did I have
my foreskin removed

121
00:04:55.563 --> 00:04:57.297
while people gave speeches
and ate lox?

122
00:04:57.430 --> 00:04:59.133
The point is.

123
00:04:59.267 --> 00:05:01.669
they love that water heater.
and who are we to question it?

124
00:05:01.803 --> 00:05:04.471
Isaac. maybe just don't mention
this to the basement ghosts.

125
00:05:04.605 --> 00:05:06.473
They are gonna figure it out

126
00:05:06.607 --> 00:05:08.676
when Mark shows up
with a new water heater.

127
00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:11.112
I know. but until then.
I don't need them complaining

128
00:05:11.245 --> 00:05:12.613
and trying to talk me out of it.

129
00:05:12.747 --> 00:05:14.414
I don't know. Samantha.
I don't feel right

130
00:05:14.549 --> 00:05:17.652
withholding information from
those ghouls. I mean. my people.

131
00:05:19.287 --> 00:05:20.420
What if I agree
to wear the button?

132
00:05:20.555 --> 00:05:22.190
Deal!

133
00:05:23.591 --> 00:05:24.926
Hey. What are you
still doing here?

134
00:05:25.059 --> 00:05:27.460
Oh. uh. since they're so busy.

135
00:05:27.595 --> 00:05:29.030
Sam asked me to stick around

136
00:05:29.163 --> 00:05:31.464
and help out with ghost stuff
for a few days.

137
00:05:31.599 --> 00:05:33.501
Thor wanted rams' testicles.

138
00:05:33.634 --> 00:05:35.002
so I'm making Swedish meatballs

139
00:05:35.136 --> 00:05:36.871
and hoping he can't smell
the difference.

140
00:05:37.004 --> 00:05:39.040
-Who you talking to?
-Sass is here.

141
00:05:39.173 --> 00:05:41.175
Oh. hey. babe.

142
00:05:41.309 --> 00:05:42.977
Loved our balloon ride
last night.

143
00:05:43.110 --> 00:05:44.946
We gave those Martians
quite a show.

144
00:05:45.079 --> 00:05:47.014
Great.

145
00:05:47.148 --> 00:05:48.015
Okay. this is perfect.

146
00:05:48.149 --> 00:05:49.116
Would you mind asking Bela

147
00:05:49.250 --> 00:05:50.551
if she's free to join me

148
00:05:50.685 --> 00:05:52.419
on a double date
with Pete and Alberta today?

149
00:05:52.553 --> 00:05:54.889
This isn't something that can
wait until Bela takes a nap?

150
00:05:55.022 --> 00:05:57.825
Oh. does Sass want to meet up?
I had lasagna for lunch--

151
00:05:57.959 --> 00:06:00.194
ugh. heavy-- so I could
see myself falling asleep

152
00:06:00.328 --> 00:06:01.361
within the hour.

153
00:06:01.494 --> 00:06:04.665
Cool.
Um. he's actually asking

154
00:06:04.799 --> 00:06:07.367
if you want to double date
with Alberta and Pete today.

155
00:06:07.501 --> 00:06:09.136
Like. in a dream?

156
00:06:09.270 --> 00:06:11.539
Oh. no. no. no.
like an actual double date

157
00:06:11.672 --> 00:06:14.374
while we're awake. It's not like
we're just a night couple.

158
00:06:14.508 --> 00:06:16.811
He's saying an actual date.
here. while you're awake.

159
00:06:16.944 --> 00:06:19.680
Okay. fun.
But how would that work?

160
00:06:19.814 --> 00:06:22.550
Well. Kyle.
this is where you come in.

161
00:06:22.683 --> 00:06:25.319
Oh. No. no.

162
00:06:25.452 --> 00:06:28.322
No. no. I will not
be acting as translator

163
00:06:28.455 --> 00:06:29.757
on a ghost double date.

164
00:06:29.891 --> 00:06:32.193
Oh. come on. Kyle. please.

165
00:06:32.326 --> 00:06:34.562
Sass and I have never
been on a real date before.

166
00:06:34.695 --> 00:06:36.030
Oh. okay. that is not true.

167
00:06:36.163 --> 00:06:37.531
We've gone on
plenty of real dates.

168
00:06:37.665 --> 00:06:39.399
They're just...

169
00:06:39.533 --> 00:06:40.400
Please. Kyle?

170
00:06:40.534 --> 00:06:41.736
It would mean a lot to us.

171
00:06:41.869 --> 00:06:44.272
Okay. fine. fine.
I will join

172
00:06:44.404 --> 00:06:47.074
as the fifth wheel on an
interdimensional ghost date.

173
00:06:47.208 --> 00:06:49.944
all because I was knocked out
by a goose on a roller coaster.

174
00:06:50.077 --> 00:06:51.411
- That's the spirit.
- Now. do these

175
00:06:51.545 --> 00:06:53.915
look like rams' balls to you?

176
00:06:54.048 --> 00:06:55.448
- Oh. yeah.
- Awesome.

177
00:06:55.583 --> 00:06:57.218
Love my life.
I'll see you later.

178
00:07:00.688 --> 00:07:02.223
Hi.
Isaac Higgintoot.

179
00:07:02.356 --> 00:07:04.191
running for
ghost representative.

180
00:07:04.325 --> 00:07:06.894
Seriously?
It's me. Catherine.

181
00:07:07.028 --> 00:07:09.263
We've been standing
next to each other for months.

182
00:07:09.397 --> 00:07:10.965
Oh.

183
00:07:11.098 --> 00:07:12.566
Oh. it's just that
you look so different.

184
00:07:12.700 --> 00:07:14.201
Is that a new sack?

185
00:07:14.335 --> 00:07:17.437
It really brings out
the jaundice in your cheeks.

186
00:07:17.571 --> 00:07:20.207
Not surprised
he doesn't recognize you.

187
00:07:20.341 --> 00:07:23.377
since he spends
all his time upstairs

188
00:07:23.511 --> 00:07:25.613
talking to his
high-altitude friends.

189
00:07:25.746 --> 00:07:27.148
Ooh. sick burn.

190
00:07:27.281 --> 00:07:30.584
-Ha! Carpetbagger.
-No. no. no. no. no.

191
00:07:30.718 --> 00:07:32.954
I am a basement ghost.
I'm creepy.

192
00:07:33.087 --> 00:07:35.623
I smell bad. People
don't want to be around me.

193
00:07:35.756 --> 00:07:38.059
I'm one of you.

194
00:07:38.192 --> 00:07:40.628
Look. Isaac. I wanted to give
you the benefit of the doubt

195
00:07:40.761 --> 00:07:42.797
when you started
this whole thing. but a leopard

196
00:07:42.930 --> 00:07:44.799
doesn't change its spots.

197
00:07:44.932 --> 00:07:47.601
You're upstairs
every chance you get.

198
00:07:47.735 --> 00:07:49.971
He was upstairs 15 minutes ago.

199
00:07:50.104 --> 00:07:52.472
You reek of sunlight
and circulated air.

200
00:07:52.606 --> 00:07:53.975
Okay. it's true.

201
00:07:54.108 --> 00:07:56.444
I do spend time up there.

202
00:07:56.577 --> 00:07:58.813
but it's for you.

203
00:07:58.946 --> 00:08:00.114
- Okay.
- No. no. no. no.

204
00:08:00.247 --> 00:08:01.916
For real. for real. In fact.

205
00:08:02.049 --> 00:08:04.719
because I have ingratiated
myself and earned their trust.

206
00:08:04.852 --> 00:08:07.487
I have come across some intel.
the likes of which

207
00:08:07.621 --> 00:08:09.156
Dirk could never glean.

208
00:08:09.290 --> 00:08:11.826
That's Creepy Dirk to you.
Show some respect.

209
00:08:11.959 --> 00:08:13.594
Wait. what are you
talking about? What intel?

210
00:08:13.728 --> 00:08:15.763
Sam and Jay

211
00:08:15.896 --> 00:08:17.832
intend to replace
the water heater.

212
00:08:17.965 --> 00:08:19.266
Yes. but

213
00:08:19.400 --> 00:08:21.168
if elected your
ghost representative.

214
00:08:21.302 --> 00:08:22.870
I won't let that happen.

215
00:08:23.004 --> 00:08:26.674
I. Isaac Higgintoot. will save

216
00:08:26.807 --> 00:08:29.176
the water heater!

217
00:08:29.310 --> 00:08:31.345
Isaac! Isaac!

218
00:08:31.479 --> 00:08:35.850
Isaac! Isaac! Isaac! Isaac!

219
00:08:40.087 --> 00:08:43.024
-Oh. greetings. all.
-Oh. you're in a good mood.

220
00:08:43.157 --> 00:08:46.027
Have you ever had
your name chanted at you?

221
00:08:46.160 --> 00:08:47.395
It's intoxicating.

222
00:08:47.528 --> 00:08:49.830
They chanted my name
at Scores once.

223
00:08:49.964 --> 00:08:51.565
They have to if you order
the Boob Luge.

224
00:08:51.699 --> 00:08:55.169
Isaac. what did you do
to receive such adulation?

225
00:08:55.302 --> 00:08:57.204
Well. that's what I'm here
to talk about.

226
00:08:57.338 --> 00:08:58.906
Samantha. there's been
a change of plans.

227
00:08:59.040 --> 00:09:00.641
- In terms of...?
- The water heater.

228
00:09:00.775 --> 00:09:03.144
You actually now
cannot buy a new one.

229
00:09:03.277 --> 00:09:04.979
What are you talking about?

230
00:09:05.112 --> 00:09:06.380
Well. as it turns out.

231
00:09:06.515 --> 00:09:07.915
my campaign was barreling
towards defeat.

232
00:09:08.049 --> 00:09:09.250
Apparently.
I'm viewed as somewhat

233
00:09:09.383 --> 00:09:11.018
of an elite
upstairs intellectual.

234
00:09:11.152 --> 00:09:14.021
So. in a shrewd
political maneuver.

235
00:09:14.155 --> 00:09:16.557
I promised
my subterranean constituents

236
00:09:16.690 --> 00:09:18.926
that their beloved water heater
shall not be replaced.

237
00:09:19.060 --> 00:09:20.728
This is unbelievable.

238
00:09:20.861 --> 00:09:22.196
Isaac promised
the basement ghosts

239
00:09:22.329 --> 00:09:23.731
that we wouldn't get
a new water heater.

240
00:09:23.864 --> 00:09:25.366
Well. what if I said
that I don't care

241
00:09:25.499 --> 00:09:26.867
what one invisible person

242
00:09:27.001 --> 00:09:29.504
promises another group
of invisible people?

243
00:09:29.637 --> 00:09:32.940
Please. Samantha. I need this
election. It means everything.

244
00:09:33.074 --> 00:09:34.742
And we need
a working water heater.

245
00:09:34.875 --> 00:09:36.577
We have guests.
and the current one

246
00:09:36.710 --> 00:09:37.912
can't keep up with the demand.

247
00:09:38.045 --> 00:09:41.182
Or we could simply pour one bath

248
00:09:41.315 --> 00:09:43.184
and allow your guests
to take turns.

249
00:09:43.317 --> 00:09:45.152
That is how
we bathed our hounds.

250
00:09:45.286 --> 00:09:47.955
Not the show hounds. obviously.
but the pigeon hounds.

251
00:09:48.089 --> 00:09:50.458
Okay. it seems that
we're at an impasse. mm?

252
00:09:50.591 --> 00:09:52.393
I need to sew up
this nomination.

253
00:09:52.527 --> 00:09:54.028
you need this new water heater.

254
00:09:54.161 --> 00:09:55.896
Or we just go
with Hetty's hound plan.

255
00:09:56.030 --> 00:09:57.631
which is still on the table.

256
00:09:57.765 --> 00:09:59.733
What if-- hm--

257
00:09:59.867 --> 00:10:02.103
we just delay
the water heater by a day?

258
00:10:02.236 --> 00:10:03.938
That way. I can tell
the basement ghosts

259
00:10:04.071 --> 00:10:05.940
that I convinced you
not to touch the old one.

260
00:10:06.073 --> 00:10:07.441
And then. after I win
the election.

261
00:10:07.576 --> 00:10:09.276
we can bring in
the new water heater.

262
00:10:09.410 --> 00:10:10.945
But won't they just
be mad later?

263
00:10:11.078 --> 00:10:12.613
Well. then I'll deal
with that then.

264
00:10:12.746 --> 00:10:14.381
The important thing
is to win the election first.

265
00:10:14.516 --> 00:10:16.217
Or you could just be
a real leader

266
00:10:16.350 --> 00:10:18.119
and tell your constituents
the hard truth now.

267
00:10:18.252 --> 00:10:20.254
Oh. like you're a profile
in courage

268
00:10:20.387 --> 00:10:21.956
when you tell Jay
that your moisturizer

269
00:10:22.089 --> 00:10:23.891
costs only eight dollars.

270
00:10:24.024 --> 00:10:25.993
Uh. Jay. now I'm thinking

271
00:10:26.127 --> 00:10:28.462
maybe we should delay the water
heater installation by a day.

272
00:10:28.597 --> 00:10:30.064
Oh. why. babe?

273
00:10:30.197 --> 00:10:32.099
Ghost stuff.

274
00:10:34.034 --> 00:10:36.637
Uh. circle? Uh. moon?
Uh. planet!

275
00:10:36.770 --> 00:10:38.139
Man. they're good.

276
00:10:38.272 --> 00:10:41.075
Bela. are you having fun?
Kyle. please relay.

277
00:10:41.208 --> 00:10:44.445
Uh. so are you having fun?
Sass is asking.

278
00:10:44.579 --> 00:10:46.147
Totally.

279
00:10:46.280 --> 00:10:47.481
I mean. I'm looking
at an empty room.

280
00:10:47.616 --> 00:10:48.816
but when it's our turn.

281
00:10:48.949 --> 00:10:50.151
I think it's gonna be
pretty exciting.

282
00:10:50.317 --> 00:10:52.319
Uh. ape.
<i>Planet of the Apes.</i>

283
00:10:52.453 --> 00:10:54.989
Ding. ding. ding. ding!
Point. "Beauty and the Pete."

284
00:10:56.056 --> 00:10:58.259
Okay. Sass and Bela. you're up.

285
00:10:58.392 --> 00:11:00.161
Bela. it's your turn to guess.

286
00:11:00.294 --> 00:11:02.696
so. Sass. here is your clue.

287
00:11:02.830 --> 00:11:05.332
Lime? What the hell
kind of clue is lime?

288
00:11:05.466 --> 00:11:06.867
Oh. he can't say it out loud.
that's cheating.

289
00:11:07.001 --> 00:11:08.836
-She can't hear me. Pete.
-Right.

290
00:11:08.969 --> 00:11:10.838
Uh. what's wrong with my clue?
Limes were my favorite garnish.

291
00:11:10.971 --> 00:11:13.374
So. quit whining
and start miming.

292
00:11:13.508 --> 00:11:14.875
Ooh. babe. that was good.

293
00:11:15.009 --> 00:11:17.178
Is the date
still happening. or...

294
00:11:17.311 --> 00:11:19.680
Kyle. put 60 seconds
on the clock.

295
00:11:21.315 --> 00:11:22.216
Kyle?

296
00:11:22.349 --> 00:11:25.953
Uh... Fine.

297
00:11:26.086 --> 00:11:27.855
-Go.
-Uh...

298
00:11:29.190 --> 00:11:30.525
Screwing in a lightbulb?

299
00:11:30.659 --> 00:11:32.627
Why are you twisting
your hand like that?

300
00:11:32.760 --> 00:11:34.461
This is how you get it
out of the tree.

301
00:11:34.596 --> 00:11:37.632
-Nuh-uh. no verbal cues.
-Is it a squirrel?

302
00:11:37.765 --> 00:11:39.300
Who pulls a squirrel off a tree?

303
00:11:39.433 --> 00:11:42.203
Uh. okay. Uh. try this.

304
00:11:42.336 --> 00:11:44.738
-Uh. turning a doorknob?
-No. Uh...

305
00:11:44.872 --> 00:11:46.006
Oh. Cleaning a glass?

306
00:11:47.141 --> 00:11:48.209
Wait. w-why'd you stop doing it?

307
00:11:48.342 --> 00:11:49.810
She's not getting it.

308
00:11:49.944 --> 00:11:51.378
Okay. maybe. uh. charades
wasn't the best idea.

309
00:11:51.513 --> 00:11:53.347
It's fine.
We got it. Pete.

310
00:11:54.516 --> 00:11:55.816
What's happening now?

311
00:11:55.950 --> 00:11:57.218
Sass is kind of
snapping at Pete.

312
00:11:57.351 --> 00:11:58.385
Well. don't tell her that.

313
00:11:58.520 --> 00:12:00.854
Look. this was a lot of fun.

314
00:12:00.988 --> 00:12:03.224
but maybe we just call it a day?

315
00:12:03.357 --> 00:12:05.192
I think we just need
a different clue. okay?

316
00:12:05.326 --> 00:12:06.528
Kyle really wasn't
getting that one.

317
00:12:06.661 --> 00:12:08.597
I'm doing it exactly
how you're...

318
00:12:08.729 --> 00:12:10.264
How is this not juicing a lime?

319
00:12:10.397 --> 00:12:11.498
Oh. and now.
he said it out loud.

320
00:12:11.633 --> 00:12:12.833
That's actually a point for us.

321
00:12:12.967 --> 00:12:14.068
And time.

322
00:12:14.201 --> 00:12:15.869
Oh. that was a disaster.

323
00:12:16.003 --> 00:12:17.905
-He said it was a disaster.
-Seriously?

324
00:12:18.038 --> 00:12:20.040
My God. man. show some judgment.

325
00:12:22.209 --> 00:12:25.779
All right. you two.
any final words before we vote?

326
00:12:25.913 --> 00:12:28.249
Just remember
who's responsible for saving

327
00:12:28.382 --> 00:12:31.185
our dear. dear water heater
and its precious gurgles.

328
00:12:31.318 --> 00:12:34.355
Some people
are calling me the Gurgle King.

329
00:12:34.488 --> 00:12:36.090
Yeah. they are.

330
00:12:36.223 --> 00:12:37.891
Gurgle King!

331
00:12:38.025 --> 00:12:40.595
Gurgle King! Gurgle King!

332
00:12:40.729 --> 00:12:41.929
I thought we were supposed
to install this tomorrow.

333
00:12:42.062 --> 00:12:44.231
Yeah. but me and Tracy

334
00:12:44.365 --> 00:12:46.568
are doing
this daytime date tomorrow.

335
00:12:46.701 --> 00:12:49.303
Our couples therapist thinks
it could be a game changer.

336
00:12:49.436 --> 00:12:51.606
It's a new water heater.

337
00:12:51.740 --> 00:12:53.941
Is it. though?
It could be a water softener.

338
00:12:54.074 --> 00:12:55.744
Or-or one of those
Japanese toilets.

339
00:12:55.876 --> 00:12:57.444
Anyway. I believe
we were about to vote.

340
00:12:57.579 --> 00:13:00.814
But why would there be
a new water heater if Isaac

341
00:13:00.948 --> 00:13:03.618
got Sam and Jay to agree
to keep the old one?

342
00:13:03.752 --> 00:13:05.219
I think I know what happened.

343
00:13:05.352 --> 00:13:07.656
- You do?
- Yep.

344
00:13:07.788 --> 00:13:09.890
Clear as day.

345
00:13:11.292 --> 00:13:14.328
Sam friggin' stabbed Isaac
in the back.

346
00:13:14.461 --> 00:13:17.599
You had a deal with her
and she decided to take

347
00:13:17.732 --> 00:13:20.735
a big old ten-dollar
dumperoo on it.

348
00:13:22.069 --> 00:13:25.072
That witch. How dare she.

349
00:13:25.205 --> 00:13:28.008
Let's go up there
and give all her guests cholera!

350
00:13:28.142 --> 00:13:30.311
- What?
- Yes.

351
00:13:30.444 --> 00:13:32.813
Or-or-or...

352
00:13:32.946 --> 00:13:35.149
we just let bygones be bygones?

353
00:13:37.985 --> 00:13:40.655
I kid. of course.
Let's do the cholera thing.

354
00:13:40.789 --> 00:13:42.823
Yeah! Cholera!

355
00:13:42.956 --> 00:13:46.093
- Cholera! Cholera!
- Cholera.

356
00:13:50.130 --> 00:13:52.366
Oh. yeah. Mom.
no. things are good. Well...

357
00:13:52.499 --> 00:13:54.868
we did have to splurge
on a new water heater.

358
00:13:55.002 --> 00:13:58.339
but hopefully. that is the last
surprise for a little while.

359
00:13:58.472 --> 00:14:00.809
Huh? Bela?
Dating anyone?

360
00:14:00.941 --> 00:14:03.210
Um. not that I've... seen.

361
00:14:03.344 --> 00:14:05.379
Oh. that's clever.
Good one. Steve.

362
00:14:05.513 --> 00:14:08.215
All right. you three
head up to the guest rooms

363
00:14:08.349 --> 00:14:10.484
and cholera anyone with a pulse.

364
00:14:10.618 --> 00:14:13.220
The rest of us will fan out
on the main floor.

365
00:14:13.354 --> 00:14:14.888
What's going on?

366
00:14:15.022 --> 00:14:17.191
Well. uh. funny story. actually.
Samantha betrayed us.

367
00:14:17.324 --> 00:14:18.959
so we're sort of up here

368
00:14:19.093 --> 00:14:22.229
to take revenge by. you know.
giving everyone cholera.

369
00:14:22.363 --> 00:14:24.532
Wait. because

370
00:14:24.666 --> 00:14:26.033
they're getting
a new water heater?

371
00:14:26.166 --> 00:14:29.136
It's not just that.
It's that she deceived us

372
00:14:29.269 --> 00:14:30.971
and broke her promise to Isaac.

373
00:14:31.105 --> 00:14:33.140
Broke her promise to Isaac?

374
00:14:33.273 --> 00:14:35.209
That doesn't sound
like something Sam would do.

375
00:14:35.342 --> 00:14:36.977
And yet here we are.

376
00:14:37.111 --> 00:14:40.047
Now. let's get to
cholera-ing everyone

377
00:14:40.180 --> 00:14:42.717
and ruining
Sam and Jay's business.

378
00:14:42.851 --> 00:14:45.486
I just feel like with Woodstone
getting on that B and B list.

379
00:14:45.620 --> 00:14:47.822
things are finally
turning around for us.

380
00:14:47.955 --> 00:14:51.425
-Now. let's make them pay.
-Yeah!

381
00:14:51.559 --> 00:14:53.093
Isaac. do something.

382
00:14:53.227 --> 00:14:55.329
Sam and Jay are your friends.

383
00:14:55.462 --> 00:14:58.399
Here we go.
Ducks on the pond.

384
00:14:58.533 --> 00:15:00.568
Hope your toilets
are working better

385
00:15:00.702 --> 00:15:02.035
than your water heater. Jay.

386
00:15:02.169 --> 00:15:04.873
No. no. no. stop this. Oh!
This is terrible.

387
00:15:05.005 --> 00:15:07.575
Wait! I lied.

388
00:15:07.709 --> 00:15:09.243
Samantha's innocent.

389
00:15:09.376 --> 00:15:11.044
What are you talking about?

390
00:15:11.178 --> 00:15:14.381
Well. um. she never promised she
would keep the old water heater.

391
00:15:14.516 --> 00:15:17.284
-I just told you that she did.
-But why?

392
00:15:17.418 --> 00:15:19.754
Because I wanted
to win the election.

393
00:15:19.888 --> 00:15:21.790
My plan was to secure your votes

394
00:15:21.922 --> 00:15:24.291
and then. well.
deal with the fallout afterward.

395
00:15:24.425 --> 00:15:28.128
So you just wanted to trick us?

396
00:15:28.262 --> 00:15:30.565
It's been 250 years.
I needed a win.

397
00:15:30.698 --> 00:15:32.232
I mean. this is crazy.

398
00:15:32.366 --> 00:15:34.435
That mouth-breather John Adams
got to become president.

399
00:15:34.569 --> 00:15:37.204
And I can't even become
a nominee to compete

400
00:15:37.337 --> 00:15:40.775
in the general election
for ghost representative.

401
00:15:40.909 --> 00:15:44.411
We almost hurt
a bunch of innocent people

402
00:15:44.546 --> 00:15:46.046
because of your lies.

403
00:15:47.080 --> 00:15:50.618
I just thank God
nobody got hurt.

404
00:15:50.752 --> 00:15:52.453
Oh. Uh-oh.

405
00:15:52.587 --> 00:15:54.121
Okay.

406
00:15:54.254 --> 00:15:56.558
that one's not on us.

407
00:15:58.560 --> 00:16:00.327
My tum-tum.

408
00:16:00.461 --> 00:16:03.665
Hey. guys. I just wanted
to come and apologize

409
00:16:03.798 --> 00:16:05.299
about the date earlier.

410
00:16:05.432 --> 00:16:06.801
Oh. hey. that's okay.

411
00:16:06.935 --> 00:16:08.803
And I'll say
what we're all thinking.

412
00:16:08.937 --> 00:16:10.638
Kyle-- he biffed it.

413
00:16:10.772 --> 00:16:13.675
Like. just copy me.
It's so easy. right?

414
00:16:13.808 --> 00:16:16.477
Like. come on.
So stupid. Kyle sucks.

415
00:16:17.478 --> 00:16:20.080
R-Right. Yeah. No. no.
It was-it was all Kyle's fault.

416
00:16:20.214 --> 00:16:22.115
Next time. I say we get Sam.

417
00:16:22.249 --> 00:16:23.818
Sam knows how to juice a lime.

418
00:16:23.952 --> 00:16:25.352
Unlike Kyle.

419
00:16:25.486 --> 00:16:27.488
Next time? There ain't
gonna be a next time.

420
00:16:27.622 --> 00:16:28.857
-Alberta.
-No. uh-uh.

421
00:16:28.989 --> 00:16:30.190
He needs some tough love.

422
00:16:30.324 --> 00:16:32.660
Baby. this wasn't Kyle's fault.

423
00:16:32.794 --> 00:16:34.361
Your girlfriend cannot see you.

424
00:16:34.495 --> 00:16:36.497
Y'all are a night couple.

425
00:16:36.631 --> 00:16:38.165
And if you think it's gonna
be anything more than that.

426
00:16:38.298 --> 00:16:39.299
you're gonna be
sorely disappointed.

427
00:16:39.433 --> 00:16:41.001
Yeah. I don't know

428
00:16:41.134 --> 00:16:42.436
if I would've shouted it
quite so bluntly.

429
00:16:42.570 --> 00:16:45.172
but. um. I do agree.

430
00:16:45.305 --> 00:16:47.341
I mean. Bela's a living woman.

431
00:16:47.474 --> 00:16:50.043
and you died 500 years ago.

432
00:16:51.278 --> 00:16:53.113
- So what are you guys saying?
- We're saying

433
00:16:53.247 --> 00:16:55.783
Bela's great. and so are you.

434
00:16:55.917 --> 00:16:58.352
but maybe you both
deserve something more.

435
00:17:01.021 --> 00:17:02.657
But Kyle's lime work...

436
00:17:02.790 --> 00:17:05.058
Oh. yeah. it definitely
left something to be desired.

437
00:17:05.192 --> 00:17:07.529
Where are you taking us?

438
00:17:07.662 --> 00:17:09.062
You'll see.

439
00:17:09.196 --> 00:17:10.532
Whoa.

440
00:17:10.665 --> 00:17:12.232
What's all this?

441
00:17:12.366 --> 00:17:14.536
It's a funeral
for the water heater.

442
00:17:14.669 --> 00:17:16.905
It doesn't make up
for what I did to you.

443
00:17:17.037 --> 00:17:18.338
and I'm not trying
to win your vote.

444
00:17:18.472 --> 00:17:19.908
I know that ship's
already sailed.

445
00:17:20.040 --> 00:17:22.644
But you all lost something
that's important to you.

446
00:17:22.777 --> 00:17:24.712
And that's worth
taking a moment to acknowledge.

447
00:17:24.846 --> 00:17:26.246
Wow.

448
00:17:26.380 --> 00:17:28.550
None of us even
had funerals for ourselves.

449
00:17:28.683 --> 00:17:29.817
and we're people.

450
00:17:29.951 --> 00:17:31.586
Arguable.

451
00:17:31.719 --> 00:17:35.222
I-I'm cold. Sam.
I'm so cold.

452
00:17:35.355 --> 00:17:36.858
He'll be better in a few hours.

453
00:17:36.991 --> 00:17:39.561
Technically.
he walked through me.

454
00:17:39.694 --> 00:17:42.429
Hurt me for a minute.
I forgive him.

455
00:17:42.564 --> 00:17:44.064
If Thor may.

456
00:17:44.197 --> 00:17:46.834
Thor have speech prepared.

457
00:17:48.468 --> 00:17:50.905
He was up all night
working on this.

458
00:17:55.208 --> 00:17:58.580
My condolences.

459
00:18:03.851 --> 00:18:05.019
Oh. I think that's it.

460
00:18:05.152 --> 00:18:06.554
That was beautiful. Thor.

461
00:18:08.056 --> 00:18:10.257
I don't know
if this is the right time.

462
00:18:10.390 --> 00:18:12.894
but my sincerest apologies
for my grandparents

463
00:18:13.027 --> 00:18:14.094
dumping you all in a mass grave.

464
00:18:14.227 --> 00:18:16.631
Oh.
That's very thoughtful.

465
00:18:16.764 --> 00:18:18.265
So you got the living butler

466
00:18:18.398 --> 00:18:20.635
to throw a funeral
for an appliance?

467
00:18:20.768 --> 00:18:22.135
I suppose I did.

468
00:18:22.269 --> 00:18:24.806
That's more than Dirk's done
in four years.

469
00:18:24.939 --> 00:18:26.774
Not my fault.

470
00:18:26.908 --> 00:18:29.443
It's hard to ask for favors
when the good-smelling lady

471
00:18:29.577 --> 00:18:32.714
refuses to talk to me because
she doesn't like being smelled.

472
00:18:32.847 --> 00:18:36.116
Isaac seems to be
really in with her.

473
00:18:36.249 --> 00:18:38.620
I mean. like.
she'll do anything for him.

474
00:18:38.753 --> 00:18:40.153
-Oh. well. I don't think...
-It's true.

475
00:18:40.287 --> 00:18:41.556
She bends to my whim.

476
00:18:41.689 --> 00:18:44.124
He got her
to write a book about him.

477
00:18:45.093 --> 00:18:46.628
Aw. screw it.

478
00:18:46.761 --> 00:18:48.896
Isaac made a mistake.
but he owned up to it.

479
00:18:49.030 --> 00:18:51.498
And who cares
if he's a pompous windbag?

480
00:18:51.633 --> 00:18:53.133
He gets results.

481
00:18:53.266 --> 00:18:56.236
Wait. what's happening?

482
00:18:56.370 --> 00:18:59.607
All in favor of Isaac
being the basement nominee?

483
00:18:59.741 --> 00:19:01.643
- Aye.
- Aye!

484
00:19:01.776 --> 00:19:03.811
Oh. my God.
I did it.

485
00:19:03.945 --> 00:19:06.346
I won. W-O-N.

486
00:19:06.480 --> 00:19:09.651
That's not my vote tally.
That's what happened.

487
00:19:11.786 --> 00:19:13.487
Please stop.

488
00:19:22.462 --> 00:19:25.298
Well. we finally
made it to Paris.

489
00:19:25.465 --> 00:19:27.367
I watched <i>Amélie</i>
and <i>Moulin Rouge</i>

490
00:19:27.502 --> 00:19:29.504
before going to bed to make sure
it worked this time.

491
00:19:32.807 --> 00:19:34.108
-We should talk...
-I've been thinking...

492
00:19:34.241 --> 00:19:35.442
- Oh. uh...
- No.

493
00:19:35.576 --> 00:19:37.011
-You first.
-O-Okay. Uh...

494
00:19:39.147 --> 00:19:42.382
Look. I really like you. but

495
00:19:42.517 --> 00:19:44.018
-I...
-But this is insane?

496
00:19:44.152 --> 00:19:45.520
Yeah.

497
00:19:45.653 --> 00:19:47.955
You're amazing and

498
00:19:48.089 --> 00:19:50.457
you deserve to be with someone
that you can interact with

499
00:19:50.591 --> 00:19:52.126
during waking hours.

500
00:19:52.259 --> 00:19:55.563
